snippet.textDisplay: The hydrogen part of the show was *quite stupide* (5:39), sorry. I think hydrogen is not a solution for EVs (bad efficiency compared to BEVs) and main train lines (better use the money to electrify lines) but it can be a good solution in other cases, eg for storage (when renewables produce too much electricity for the needs of the grid) or planes (because of the weight of batteries) or even for train lines with let's say only one train per day. But the stupide sentence was "humains don't need to breath anyway" (5:57) because in the new German trains the hydrogen is of course not burned but used to generate electricity (with a fuel cell). So the only "emission" is water while diesel trains were emitting many polluting and greenhouse gas. And what is the link with the Hindenburg ? This zeppelin was moved by 4 diesel engines, the hydrogen was not here to be burned. It is as stupid as saying that a forest is bad for air quality and regarding global warming because it can accidently burn. But of course, hydrogen must be produced with renewable energy, the hydrogen used for trains, future zeppelins, rockets, and all the industry. It will be difficult but we have no alternative since *petrol and coal and gas must stay in the ground*.
